lead_paragraph: Coach Dan McCarney resigned yesterday after 12 seasons as the Cyclones’ coach, leaving the program after one its most disappointing seasons. McCarney, the Big 12’s longest-tenured coach, will direct the Cyclones (3-7, 0-6) for their final two games of the season. He is 55-84 at Iowa State.
